JOHANNESBURG - Tripartite Alliance partner Cosatu is unhappy with the performance of Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. It says his presence has not helped sort out the problems at Eskom. READ: Cosatu blames current leadership for SA's unemployment crisis It's now calling on President Cyril Ramaphosa to take action to stabilise the situation. Cosatu's remarks come after ANC deputy president David Mabuza asserted the president was misled over problems at Eskom. READ: The president was misled about load-shedding, says Mabuza ANC Treasurer-General Paul Mashatile responded to the calls for Gordhan's removal by saying the deployment of a minister is the prerogative of the president.